                <h1>The Little Prince: A Timeless Tale of Wisdom</h1>
                <p>The Little Prince, written by Antoine de Saint-Exupéry in 1943, is a philosophical tale that explores themes of love, loss, and human nature. The story follows a young prince from a distant asteroid who travels to Earth, meeting various characters that reflect the complexities of adulthood. It emphasizes the importance of looking beyond the surface.</p>
